Io is frankly incorrect, this issue is no longer "between just them [Amber and Johnny]," Amber Turd went public with her fanaticism and made the bed she now must lay in.  Amber and her cohorts went public to destroy Depp, therefor the public has the right to comment, and in America we're also protected by the First Amendment that offers us blanket immunity to false litigation pushed by people demanding censorship and silencing of what they don't want public.  

I'm almost confident that Amber Turd has already pushed a cease and desist against Brian, he's been quiet for some time now and hasn't spoken upon the suit.  He's covered the suit accurately and all his information was from the courts and what is public, Brian conducted himself like any earnest journalist would do, he acted ethically and is protected by journalistic standards that are offered to him.  But Brian probably cannot afford to go to court through time and/or money, even though he's wholesomely in the right covering this lawsuit, but some people simply aren't able to be pulled from their lives and spend a year or two struggling to pay lawyers over a egregious wrongful cease and desist.
